The evidence with the title 'A brief history of: 'putting lipstick on a pig' - time ' says Sep 11, 2008  ... It 's a phrase common in the car sales industry, used to describe taking a hunk of junk , brushing on a fresh coat of paint and selling it for full price. Now, in the wake of Barack Obama 's use of the saying and the McCain/Palin attacks against him over it , "putting lipstick on a pig" has become the latest flashpoint  ... 
